      "updated_at": "2026-05-19T23:30:18Z",
      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "I don’t see the point of this change. These python scripts accompany written specification documents as reference implementations, they are not living code. They are not expected to be updated, so they wouldn’t break. If someone were to add to these tests at a later time, and were to run into files not being loaded at that time, they could prompt an LLM to fix it as easily then.\n\nConcept -0, I don’t think we should encourage this sort of code churn, but if you feel that it’s an improvement, please feel free to merge it, @jonatack.",
