      "created_at": "2026-06-01T23:51:50Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-06-01T23:51:50Z",
      "author_association": "NONE",
      "body": "> These python scripts accompany written specification documents as reference implementations, they are not living code.\r\n\r\nI tend to agree with this view. It's the same problem with academic papers, we don't update published code even if it does not build or run anymore with more updated tooling or system. The same for software patents (e.g. Brazil's patents office allows for registering specific versions of source code). I suggest reference code published in BIPs to be updated only if they are in error (i.e. they don't correctly implement the specification) or in case the specification itself is updated, to avoid AI PR farming.\r\n\r\nPS: I'm not suggesting this proposal is AI slop.",
      "user": {
        "login": "edilmedeiros",
        "id": 78322931,
        "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjc4MzIyOTMx",
        "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/78322931?v=4",
        "gravatar_id": "",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/users/edilmedeiros",
        "html_url": "https://github.com/edilmedeiros",
        "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/edilmedeiros/followers",
